          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                (Non-negative Property) Explain why
                <m>d(P,Q) \geq 0</m> for any two points in the plane.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                (Symmetric Property) Explain why
                <m>d(P,Q) = d(Q,P)</m> for any two points in the plane.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                (Identity Property) Show that
                <m>d(P,Q) = 0</m> <em>if and only if</em>
                <m>P</m> and <m>Q</m> are the same point.
