          </tabular>
          From the diagram, we see the horizontal distance  is
          <m>\left|x_{1} - x_{0}\right|</m> and the vertical distance is <m>\left|y_{1} - y_{0}\right|</m>,
          so the total distance the taxi needs to travel to get from <m>P</m> to <m>Q</m> is given by:
          <me>
            d_{T} =  \left|x_{1} - x_{0}\right| + \left|y_{1} - y_{0}\right|
          </me>
